The paper proposes a deep learning architecture for estimating energy expenditure using temporal foreground silhouettes and accelerometer data. This involves computer vision (silhouette extraction) and machine learning (deep learning architecture), which suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper focuses on free living monitoring in private environments, which involves human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and multimedia (cs.MM) aspects. Finally, the paper deals with energy expenditure estimation, which is a topic of interest in the field of neural engineering (cs.NE).
